---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';

const title = 'Privacy Policy';
const description = 'How StateWages collects and uses information.';
const lastUpdated = 'March 2026';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} noIndex={false}>
  <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'Privacy Policy' }]} />

  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p>Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <main>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose-content">

        <section class="section">
          <h2>What this is</h2>
          <p>
            StateWages (statewages.com) is a salary data site. This page explains what we collect and what we do with it. We don't sell your data. We don't run a mailing list you didn't sign up for.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
          <h2>Information you give us</h2>
          <p>
            If you use the contact form, we get your name and email. We use that only to reply. We don't add you to a newsletter or share that info with anyone else.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
          <h2>Information we get when you visit</h2>
          <p>
            Like most websites, we may collect basic technical data: IP address (often anonymized), browser type, which pages you looked at, how you got here. We use that to see how the site is used and fix problems. We're not building a profile on you to sell.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
          <h2>Cookies and advertising</h2>
          <p>
            We may use cookies for things like remembering preferences or understanding traffic. If we show ads on the site (for example through Google AdSense), those ads are served by the ad provider. They use their own cookies and may collect data according to their privacy policy. You can control or block cookies in your browser. Turning them off might affect how some parts of the site or ads work.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
          <h2>Third-party services</h2>
          <p>
            We may use services for analytics, hosting, or the contact form. Those companies have their own privacy policies. We don't hand over your personal information except as needed to run the site (e.g. sending your contact form submission to our email).
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
          <h2>Security</h2>
          <p>
            We take reasonable steps to keep the site and any data we hold secure. Nothing on the internet is 100% secure. We don't store payment info because we don't charge for the site.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
          <h2>Kids</h2>
          <p>
            The site isn't aimed at children under 13. We don't knowingly collect personal information from them. If you think we have, contact us and we'll remove it.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
          <h2>Links to other sites</h2>
          <p>
            We link to official sources (e.g. BLS) and maybe other sites. We're not responsible for their privacy practices. Check their policies if you care.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
          <h2>Your rights</h2>
          <p>
            Depending where you live, you may have rights to access, correct, or delete your data. To ask about that, email us. We'll do what we can.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
          <h2>Changes</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this page from time to time. The date at the top will change. Using the site after that means you're okay with the updated version.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
          <h2>Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions about privacy? Email <a href="mailto:arjungoel42@gmail.com">arjungoel42@gmail.com</a> or use the <a href="/contact/">contact form</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose-content {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 0;
  }
  .prose-content .section {
    margin-bottom: 2.25rem;
  }
  .prose-content h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
</style>
